def about_screen(info: DatasetInfo) -> None:
    print_header("Welcome to Symptom Explorer")
    print(
        f"""
What this program is:
- An educational tool that explores a synthetic medical symptom dataset.
- It can summarize common symptoms and diagnoses, generate plots, and run a simple rule-based matcher.

What it is NOT:
- It is NOT medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment guidance.

How it works:
- The dataset contains a diagnosis column ("{info.diagnosis_col}") and symptom indicator columns.
- Statistics and charts are computed from the dataset (symptom present if value > threshold).

Navigation:
- Choose menu numbers and press Enter.
- Auto-logout after 60 minutes of inactivity.
"""
    )


def help_page(role: str) -> None:
    print_header("Help: Symptom Explorer")
    print(
        """
Core features:
1) Explore dataset
   - View columns, preview rows, filter by diagnosis (list is shown).

2) Statistics (Full summary)
   - Asks only ONE question (show or save) then generates TWO charts:
     - Top symptoms chart
     - Top diagnoses chart

3) Visualizations (user-driven)
   - Choose top N, threshold, metric (count/proportion), and show or save.

4) Symptom Checker (educational)
   - Enter symptoms; program filters matching rows and shows most frequent diagnoses.

Accounts & security:
- Login or create an account inside the program.
- Password rules:
  - â‰¥ 8 characters
  - at least 1 lowercase, 1 uppercase, 1 digit, 1 special character
- Passwords stored securely using salted PBKDF2 hashing (not plaintext).

Roles:
- User:
  - Explore, stats, visuals, checker, change own password
- Admin:
  - All user features + manage users (list/add/delete/reset password)

Auto-logout:
- Session ends after 60 minutes of inactivity.
"""
    )
